Class ModuleTest

java.lang.Object
college.mtu_test.ModuleTest
public class ModuleTest extends Object
Test class for the Module class. This class tests the functionality of the Module class, which represents a module of a student in a college.

    • testValidModuleName

      public void testValidModuleName()
      Test case for getting a valid module name. This test checks if the correct module name is retrieved from the Module object.

      Test output: The expected module name. Preconditions: A valid Module object with an associated name. Test procedure: 1. Call the getModuleName() method on the Module object. 2. Verify that the returned name is the same as the expected module name.

    • testValidModuleCode

      public void testValidModuleCode()
      Test case for getting a valid module code. This test checks if the correct module code is retrieved from the Module object.

      Test output: The expected module code. Preconditions: A valid Module object with an associated code. Test procedure: 1. Call the getModuleCode() method on the Module object. 2. Call the validateModuleCode() method on the Controller object with the expected module code. 3. Verify that the returned error message is null and the retrieved module code is the same as the expected module code.

    • testInvalidModuleCode

      public void testInvalidModuleCode()
      Test case for validating an invalid module code. This test checks if an invalid module code is rejected according to the validation logic in the Controller.

      Test output: A non-null error message indicating an invalid module code. Preconditions: An invalid module object with an associated code. Test procedure: 1. Create a new Module object with an invalid module code. 2. Call the getModuleCode() method on the invalid Module object. 3. Call the validateModuleCode() method on the Controller object with the invalid module code. 4. Verify that the returned error message is not null.

    • testValidModuleSemester

      public void testValidModuleSemester()
      Test case for validating a valid module semester. This test checks if a valid semester is accepted according to the validation logic in the Controller.

      Test output: A false value indicating a valid semester. Preconditions: A valid Module object with an associated semester. Test procedure: 1. Call the getSemester() method on the Module object. 2. Call the validateSemester() method on the Controller object with the retrieved semester value. 3. Verify that the returned boolean value is false.

    • testInvalidModuleSemester

      public void testInvalidModuleSemester()
      Test case for validating an invalid module semester. This test checks if the given semester of a Module object is invalid according to the validation logic in the Controller.

      Test output: A true value indicating an invalid module semester. Preconditions: An invalid semester integer value associated with a Module object. Test procedure: 1. Create a new Module object with an invalid semester value. 2. Call the getSemester() method on the Module object to retrieve the semester value. 3. Call the validateSemester() method on the Controller object with the retrieved semester value. 4. Verify that the returned boolean value is true, indicating an invalid module semester.
